# Sifu Pangda — GDD v1.1

> **Design-provided GDD** (not a Unity port). Movement derives from `Units.cs`
> (meters·seconds). In-run character leveling was removed in v0.3.7: HP is a
> flat base and permanent growth comes from the additive HP/ATK/DEF pools.

## Character Overview

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Race | Panda |
| Role | Tank, initiator |
| Realm | Gui Lin (GL) — still requires a matching world-pool entry before starter status |
| Base HP | 300 |
| Personality | Meditating master: calm, centered, unhurried—until provoked. “Those who interrupt my XiuXing shall embrace the fiercest burn.” |

## Visual Design

**Current animation pass:** approved sheets now cover Idle, Walk, Jump, Fuhu Palm,
and Fuhu Kick. Heli actions, Drink, Bottle Throw, Hurt, and Death temporarily hold
the idle animation; the raw and unknown sheets are excluded from the game.

Future key elements: panda martial artist, Chi shield glow, hulu bottle, and clear
ground-versus-air martial-arts silhouettes.

## Passive — 气定神闲 (Qì Dìng Shén Xián)

Pangda has two stance-bound skill sets. **伏虎式 (Fuhu)** is available only while
standing on Ground or Platform. **鹤唳式 (Heli)** is available otherwise. SoftVolumes
do not count as ground, and coyote time does not preserve Fuhu access. A skill keeps
the stance selected when its input began, even if Pangda changes state before it
resolves.

| Chi-shield parameter | Value |
|---|---:|
| Damage conversion | 30% of post-mitigation damage Pangda deals |
| Maximum shield | 60 |
| Combat-inactivity grace | 3 s |
| Decay after grace | 10 shield/s |
| Immunity | None — Pangda receives damage, stun, Trapped, hazards, and knockback normally |

The base `CharacterController` owns a public `CombatInactivitySeconds` counter for
all protagonists and future wonder items. It resets when the active protagonist
lands valid damage or receives a valid damaging hit, including damage fully absorbed
by a shield. Pangda begins shield decay only once this common counter reaches 3 s.

Chi shield is a combat-transient pool: it is not carried through a Tab body swap or
between arena visits.

## Basic Attack — 降龙伏虎 (Xiáng Lóng Fú Hǔ)

The shared BA magazine applies only to Fuhu palms. Heli Dive is a contextual aerial
attack and consumes no ammo.

| Shared Fuhu magazine | Value |
|---|---:|
| Capacity / reload size | 2 / 2 |
| Attack interval | 0.6 s |
| Reload delay | 1 s after the last successful palm |
| Reload policy | Non-blocking; reload restores both palms and resets the combo |

### Fuhu — Palm Combo

Two identical palm strikes form the combo. Each strike is committed: its hit happens
after the windup, then Pangda recovers before another action.

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---:|
| Stacks | 2 |
| Forward hitbox | 4 m wide × 3 m high rectangle; begins at Pangda’s front |
| Damage | 40 per palm |
| Stun | 0.5 s |
| Windup | 0.2 s |
| Recovery | 0.4 s |
| Self lunge | 1 m forward over the first 0.2 s of recovery |
| Enemy knockback | None |

### Heli — Falling Crane

Pangda descends straight downward at a fixed speed. He passes through foes on the
way down; only a Ground or Platform landing produces the impact.

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---:|
| Dive speed | 32 m/s straight down |
| During dive | Gravity and all external velocity are ignored |
| Landing hitbox | 4 m wide × 1 m high rectangle, centered just above Pangda’s feet |
| Landing damage | 50 |
| Knock-up | 10 m/s upward delta-v |
| Stun | 0.5 s |
| Recovery | 0.5 s |
| Magazine interaction | None |

## Shift — 破竹 (Pò Zhú)

Fuhu Shift and Heli Shift each have their own cooldown. Using one does not begin,
reset, or block the other.

| Shared cooldown rule | Value |
|---|---:|
| Fuhu Shift cooldown | 8 s |
| Heli Shift cooldown | 8 s |
| Direction source | Fuhu uses facing (left/right); Heli captures the cursor direction on cast |

### Fuhu — Tiger-Subduing Kick

Pangda holds a vulnerable, non-moving windup for one second, then delivers a heavy
forward kick. He receives no immunity during the windup or hit.

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---:|
| Windup | 1 s |
| Hit region | 6 m wide × 4 m high; its bottom begins at Pangda’s feet and extends forward |
| Damage | 40 |
| Knockback | 18 m/s forward delta-v |
| Stun | 1 s |
| Recovery | None beyond the windup resolution |

### Heli — Crane Flight

Pangda dashes along the captured cursor direction. The leading 2×2 m check box stops
the dash at the first Ground, Platform, or foe it reaches. Pangda then creates an
impact square; the collision itself does not deal a separate hit.

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---:|
| Dash speed | 32 m/s |
| Maximum distance | 16 m |
| During dash | Gravity and all external velocity are ignored |
| Leading check box | 2 m × 2 m |
| Stop conditions | Ground, Platform, foe, or maximum distance |
| Impact region | 2 m × 2 m square centered at the stop point |
| Damage | 40 |
| Knockback | 16 m/s along the captured dash direction |
| Recovery | None after impact |

## E — 独酌 (Dú Zhuó)

Fuhu E and Heli E each have their own 14-second cooldown. The former two-phase E is
split across the stances: Fuhu retains the drink; Heli retains the bottle throw.

### Fuhu — Drink

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---:|
| Cooldown | 14 s (Fuhu only) |
| Duration | 1.5 s |
| Movement during drink | 40% of normal speed |
| Shield grant timing | 0.8 s |
| Shield grant | Fill Chi shield to its 60 cap |
| Other actions | BA, Shift, E, held item, and Tab switch are unavailable; movement remains available |
| Immunity | None |

### Heli — Bottle Throw

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---:|
| Cooldown | 14 s (Heli only) |
| Cast | Immediate; no drink phase |
| Projectile speed / lifetime / radius | 20 m/s / 2 s / 0.25 m |
| Projectile collision | First foe, Ground, or Platform; SoftVolumes are ignored |
| Hit damage | 25 |
| Status | 1 s Trapped |

> **Trapped.** The target has no input movement, jump, or dash; new external
> impulses are ignored; gravity continues; skills remain castable. It is a root,
> not a full stun.

## Ultimate — 归一 (Guī Yī)

**Deferred in the prototype.** The existing ultimate proposal remains a future design
