## Design Notes

- Pangda is durable through contact, not immunity. He must keep trading to retain Chi,
  while the three-second grace prevents a shield earned in a fight from disappearing
  during a short reposition.
- Fuhu is the reliable ground-control kit. Its long Shift windup deliberately gives
  foes counterplay: leave the kick region, stun Pangda, or force him into the air.
- Heli creates vertical commitment. Both aerial attacks ignore intervening foes and
  become threatening only when Pangda chooses a landing or dash line well.
- The stance-specific cooldowns reward weaving ground and air actions without making
  either individual cast immune, untargetable, or universally safe.
- The 18 m/s Fuhu kick is meaningful displacement without the old 32 m/s launch that
  could send a target across much of the arena.

## Implementation Notes

- `CharacterController.CombatInactivitySeconds` is the shared out-of-combat clock;
  it is not a Pangda-only timer and future item logic may read it.
- Chi shield overrides `AbsorbDamage`, after base Temp HP. Its generation subscribes
  to the post-mitigation `DamageDealt` event, never to incoming damage.
- Fuhu palms use the universal `AmmoController`. Heli Dive does not consume or reload
  it. The extra stance cooldown remaining values persist and tick at the same background
  rate as the existing Shift/E cooldowns.
- Fixed Heli movement is an explicit character state that supplies its own velocity;
  it does not write a one-time external impulse or depend on gravity.
- The bottle is a player projectile and reports its post-mitigation damage through
  Pangda’s standard damage-dealt path while its owner is active.
- `SifuPangda.tscn` now drives approved sheets through `UpdateAnimator`: Idle, Walk,
  Jump, Fuhu Palm, and Fuhu Kick. Heli Dive, Heli Dash, Drink, Bottle Throw, Hurt,
  and Death remain idle fallbacks until their final sheets are ready; raw source
  sheets are deliberately not used at runtime. Gameplay timing and hit calls remain
  in code at their existing state-transition markers.
- With debug ranges enabled, Fuhu shows both its Palm and larger Shift rectangles;
  Falling Crane shows its feet-aligned knock-up region while airborne, brightening
  during an active dive. Every rectangle is derived from the same balance row as its hit.

## QA Acceptance Cases

- Ground/Platform selects Fuhu; air and SoftVolumes select Heli; coyote time does not
  preserve Fuhu access.
- Each stance’s Shift/E cooldown remains independent through use, Tab switch, bench
  ticking, save/load, and return to the stance.
- Chi gains only from post-mitigation dealt damage, caps at 60, and starts decaying
  exactly after 3 seconds without valid damage dealt or received.
- A fully shielded incoming hit resets combat inactivity; rejected invulnerable hits do not.
- Heli BA passes through foes and hits only once on a terrain landing. Heli Shift stops
  at its leading check box and applies one impact hit along the captured direction.
- Fuhu Drink leaves Pangda damageable and blocks all actions except movement; Bottle
  Throw roots the first foe hit and expires safely on terrain or lifetime.

## Image Generation Prompts

**TODO — deferred.** Future sprite sheets must cover: Heli Dive, Heli Dash, Drink,
Bottle Throw, Hurt, and Death. Final Fuhu Kick art may split its windup and hit later.

## Decisions Log

- **Two stance-bound kits replace immunity stacking.** Pangda’s defense is earned by
  sustained contact and proactive positioning, not uninterrupted invulnerability.
- **Out-of-combat decay uses a shared protagonist clock.** Items and future passives
  need the same “away from battle” fact; duplicating a Pangda timer would guarantee drift.
- **Fuhu Shift is vulnerable and 18 m/s.** The one-second windup supplies readable
  counterplay, while the reduced push avoids arena-spanning displacement.
- **Air attacks resolve on terrain or dash impact.** This makes altitude, platforms,
  and aim meaningful instead of turning Heli into a second free melee combo.
- **Ultimate is deferred, not removed.** The global ultimate economy is still TBD; no
  Pangda-specific implementation should predetermine it.

